{"TopicId":152824,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"GPS, spare parts...","CreatedByName":"Darnok","CreatedById":85708,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-01T15:11:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Darnok","CreatedById":85708,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-01T15:11:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe have \u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ELongitude\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan\u003Eand\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan\u003ELatitude in game visible since day 1, IMO we should have access to GPS only if we are in range of GPS satellites/transmitters.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis would require one new part \u0022GPS module\u0022 for GPS satellites, no additional part on vehicle (probe core would solve it with new feature). If your craft is in range of at least 2-3 GPS satellites then you can see \u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ELongitude\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan\u003Eand\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan\u003ELatitude. Depends on orbit (range from our craft) of GPS satellites we could have different accuracy (degrees, minutes, seconds).\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EIn career mode it would give us new contracts \u0022cover area X with GPS\u0022.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSometimes GPS module could fail and it would require to be serviced by engineer. Repairs should be possible only from command seat and craft equipped with \u0022spare parts box\u0022. This mechanic could be used for lots of new things for example drills could also fail from time to time...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-01T16:00:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222870734\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480605096\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002285708\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Darnok\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, Darnok said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe have \u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ELongitude\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan\u003Eand\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan\u003ELatitude in game visible since day 1, IMO we should have access to GPS only if we are in range of GPS satellites/transmitters.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLong before the days of artificial satellites, the Ancient Ones were already measuring \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sextant\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Elatitudes\u003C/a\u003E and \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marine_chronometer\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Elongitudes\u003C/a\u003E (to varying degrees of accuracy)...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Darnok","CreatedById":85708,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-01T16:21:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222870801\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480608011\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLong before the days of artificial satellites, the Ancient Ones were already measuring \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sextant\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Elatitudes\u003C/a\u003E and \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marine_chronometer\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Elongitudes\u003C/a\u003E (to varying degrees of accuracy)...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure, but they didn\u0027t had reading live driving 30m/s \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-01T20:49:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/22673-10-figaro-global-navigation-satellite-system-launch-a-working-gps-system/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hms_warrior","CreatedById":142205,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-02T07:50:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nuhm....can\u0027t you just stick a probe core on your vessel/rover and activate kerbNet? imho it gives you your position (well, actualy the position of the cursor, but the cursor starts centered at your vessels position by default).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}